question: What is the capital of Commonwealth of Dominica?
explanation: Dominica, officially the Commonwealth of Dominica, is an island country located in the Caribbean Sea. It is a part of the Windward Islands of the Lesser Antilles archipelago of the Caribbean Sea. In the Eastern Caribbean Sea, the island country of Dominica is located about halfway between the French islands of Guadeloupe (to the north) and Martinique (to the south). The capital of Dominica is Roseau.
